Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: thin-film solid oxide fuel cells were evaluated between 650 and 800 degreesC. Peak power densities and power densities at cell voltages of 0.7 V were 320 and 190 mW/cm(2), respectively, at 650 degreesC, denoted as 320/190/650.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: Corresponding power densities at other temperature were 1400/1100/800, 990/640/750, and 600/360/700.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: At 750 degreesC and lower, the power densities and ASRs (area-specific resistances) were better than those reported for an 8YSZ cell with record performance [S. de Souza, S.J. Visco, L.C. De Jonghe, in Proceeding of the Second European Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Forum, edited by B. Thorstensen, vol. 2 (1996), 677.], while showing a smaller temperature dependence.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: Further performance improvements of about a factor of 2 were obtained at 650 degreesC after infiltration of the LSM/YSZ cathodes with a cobalt solution.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: This improvement persisted up to about 750 degreesC, being more pronounced at the lower temperatures.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: The results indicate the potential benefit of cobalt infiltration for reduced temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: AC measurements revealed that the majority of effect resulted from a decrease in the non-ohmic resistance of the cathode.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: TEM observations found similar to25 nm Co3O4 particles in the pores of the modified LSM-composite cathodes.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes

Sentencas: The AC impedance response following cobalt infiltration indicates a decrease of the effective charge transfer resistance.
Titulo: Thin film SOFCs with cobalt-infiltrated cathodes
